From b0a0cedd7bd174366c1e63a32f491b555c58c6c4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: thoran <machagadu6@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 20:04:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] refactor(auth): unify forgot/reset and authenticated
 change-password

passwordController (forgot-password / verify-code / reset) and
userPasswordController (verify-current / update / legacy) now emit
the canonical envelope. Replaces the inline { success, error }
shapes and the { error, code } shape that omitted the success
flag.

Behaviour preserved end-to-end:
  - request-reset still returns the privacy-preserving generic
    message regardless of whether the email exists
  - update still revokes every other session via authService.logoutAll
    and clears the trusted-device cookie
  - legacyPasswordHandler still routes legacy single-payload calls
    to verify or update as appropriate
